modules.description: Processes strings in a specified encoding by folding over each character with its position. Works with `string` and `Rosetta.encoding` types. Useful for parsing or transforming encoded text where character positions are significant, such as in compilers or text editors.

This module handles character encoding conversion and decoding of input sources like strings or channels. It provides functions to decode input into Unicode characters, track byte positions, and identify the encoding of a stream. Concrete use cases include parsing encoded text files, handling user input in different encodings, and implementing custom text processing pipelines.
